===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Originally written {{zh-l|*𦎫}} in {{w|oracle bone script}} and {{w|bronze script}}, an {{Han compound|亯|羊|ls=ic|t1=ancestral shrine|t2=sheep|nocap=yes}}. According to Ma Rusen (馬如森), the character represents a cooked goat used as a sacrifice. According to Ma Xulun (馬敍倫) and Yang Shuda (楊樹達), the character's original meanings was "to cook" and is the original form of [[燉]].

Later used to mean “to force; to compel” and came to be written with {{zh-l|*攴}}, making the modern form an {{Han compound|𦎫|攴|ls=ic|ls2=psc|c1=p|c2=s|t2=hand|nocap=yes}}. The character [[燉]] was graphically shaped after the modern version.

